{
  "id": "feature-perf-012-image-lazy-loading",
  "title": "Add Lazy Loading and Error Handling to All Image Elements",
  "category": "Performance",
  "description": "## Problem\nAll `<img>` tags in the application use basic rendering without `loading=\"lazy\"`, placeholder states, or error handling. This means all images (feature screenshots, project icons, description images) load immediately when their container renders, even if they're off-screen. Failed image loads show broken image icons.\n\n## Current Behavior\nImage elements across the codebase follow this pattern:\n```tsx\n// dashboard-view.tsx lines 766-773\n<img\n  src={getAuthenticatedImageUrl(project.customIconPath, project.path)}\n  alt={project.name}\n  className=\"w-full h-full object-cover\"\n/>\n```\n\nNo `loading=\"lazy\"`, no placeholder, no error handling.\n\n## Locations with <img> Tags (20+ locations):\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx` (lines 2180, 2267) - Feature images\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/dashboard-view.tsx` (lines 766, 857) - Project icons\n- `apps/ui/src/components/ui/description-image-dropzone.tsx` (lines 493, 499) - Description images\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/agent-view/components/message-bubble.tsx` (line 157) - Chat images\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/kanban-card/card-content-sections.tsx` - Feature card images\n- `apps/ui/src/components/ui/feature-image-upload.tsx` - Image upload previews\n- Plus 15+ other locations\n\n## Required Changes\n\n### 1. Add `loading=\"lazy\"` to All Off-Screen Images\nSimplest change with biggest impact. Native browser lazy loading defers loading of off-screen images.\n\n### 2. Create a Reusable `<LazyImage>` Component\n```typescript\n// apps/ui/src/components/ui/lazy-image.tsx\nfunction LazyImage({ src, alt, className, fallback, ...props }) {\n  const [status, setStatus] = useState<'loading' | 'loaded' | 'error'>('loading');\n  \n  return (\n    <div className={cn('relative', className)}>\n      {status === 'loading' && (\n        <div className=\"absolute inset-0 bg-muted animate-pulse rounded\" />\n      )}\n      {status === 'error' && (\n        <div className=\"absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center bg-muted rounded\">\n          <ImageOff className=\"w-6 h-6 text-muted-foreground\" />\n        </div>\n      )}\n      <img\n        src={src}\n        alt={alt}\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        onLoad={() => setStatus('loaded')}\n        onError={() => setStatus('error')}\n        className={cn('transition-opacity', status === 'loaded' ? 'opacity-100' : 'opacity-0')}\n        {...props}\n      />\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Add Placeholder Skeletons During Image Load\nUse CSS `aspect-ratio` to prevent layout shift while images load.\n\n### 4. Add Error State for Failed Images\nShow a sensible fallback instead of broken image icon.\n\n## Files to Modify\n- Create: `apps/ui/src/components/ui/lazy-image.tsx` - Reusable lazy image component\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx` - Replace `<img>` with `<LazyImage>`\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/dashboard-view.tsx` - Replace `<img>` with `<LazyImage>`\n- `apps/ui/src/components/ui/description-image-dropzone.tsx` - Replace `<img>` with `<LazyImage>`\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/agent-view/components/message-bubble.tsx` - Replace `<img>` with `<LazyImage>`\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/kanban-card/card-content-sections.tsx`\n- `apps/ui/src/components/ui/feature-image-upload.tsx`\n- All other files with `<img>` tags\n\n## Expected Impact\n- Off-screen images no longer fetched until user scrolls to them\n- Smoother page load with skeleton placeholders instead of blank spaces\n- Better UX when images fail to load (clear error state vs broken icon)\n- Reduced initial bandwidth usage\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- All images use `loading=\"lazy\"` or the `<LazyImage>` component\n- Skeleton placeholder visible while images load\n- Error state shows fallback icon when images fail to load\n- No Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) - images have defined dimensions/aspect-ratio\n- Board view with many feature images scrolls without loading all images upfront\n- Existing image functionality (click to preview, zoom, etc.) still works",
  "images": [],
  "imagePaths": [],
